<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="845" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14552.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-11T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Answering your March 10, 4 p.m., the various representatives bring the
                            troubles of their nationals to us and we have been anxious to do all we
                            could to help them, but if our efforts provoke protest <pb facs="0786" n="670" xml:id="pg_670"/> from Carranza it is better to have the
                            effort made through local representatives of their nations. You will
                            however please assist these local representatives by counsel and advise
                            and in any other way possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>